r>1983\u201384</center>\n|[[Dynamo Dresden]]\n|<center>2\u20131</center>\n|[[BFC Dynamo]]\n|-\n|<center>[[1984\u201385 FDGB-Pokal|1984\u201385]]</center>\n|[[Dynamo Dresden]]\n|<center>3\u20132</center>\n|[[BFC Dynamo]]\n|-\n|<center>1985\u201386</center>\n|[[1. FC Lokomotive Leipzig|FC Lokomotive Leipzig]]\n|<center>5\u20131</center>\n|[[1. FC Union Berlin|FC Union Berlin]]\n|-\n|<center>1986\u201387</center>\n|[[1. FC Lokomotive Leipzig|FC Lokomotive Leipzig]]\n|<center>4\u20131</center>\n|[[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]]\n|-\n|<center>[[1987\u201388 FDGB-Pokal|1987\u201388]]</center>\n|[[BFC Dynamo]]\n|<center>2\u20130 ([[Overtime (sports)|a.e.t.]])</center>\n|[[FC Carl Zeiss Jena|Carl Zeiss Jena]]\n|-\n|<center>[[1988\u201389 FDGB-Pokal|1988\u201389]]</center>\n|[[BFC Dynamo]]\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|[[Chemnitzer FC|FC Karl-Marx-Stadt]]\n|-\n|<center>[[1989\u201390 FDGB-Pokal|1989\u201390]]</center>\n|[[Dynamo Dresden]]\n|<center>2\u20131</center>\n|[[FC Mecklenburg Schwerin|Dynamo Schwerin]]\n|-\n|<center>[[1990\u201391 NOFV-Pokal|1990\u201391]]</center>\n|[[F.C. Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]]\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|[[Eisenh\u00fcttenst\u00e4dter FC Stahl]]\n|}\n\n==Performances==\n===Performance by club===\nThe performance of various clubs is shown in the following table: <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrcuphist.html|title=East Germany - List of Cup Finals|author=|date=|website=www.rsssf.com|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref><br>\n''Clubs are named by the last name they used before the [[German reunification]].''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n! style=\"width:22%;\"| Club\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Winners\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Runners-up\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Semi-finalists\n! Winning Years\n|-\n| [[SG Dynamo Dresden]] <sup>1</sup>\n| <center>'''7'''</center>\n| <center>4</center>\n| <center>6</center>\n| 1952, 1971, 1977, 1982, 1984, 1985, 1990\n|-\n| [[1. FC Magdeburg]] <sup>2</sup>\n|